title: Veteran of Indy banking to lead Lake City division
text:
Home » Veteran of Indy banking to lead Lake City division Veteran of Indy banking to lead Lake City division October 17, 2015 CFO of the Year 
Warsaw-based Lake City Bank last month appointed Bill Redman to lead its Indianapolis commercial banking team. Redman, who has worked in Indianapolis banking since 1987, was most recently vice president and commercial banking manager with the National Bank of Indianapolis. His title at Lake City is senior vice president and regional commercial banking manager.“Our progress in the Indianapolis market has established a strong reputation for Lake City Bank and we’ve been very pleased with our successful growth in the market,” CEO David Findlay said in a statement.•
